<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 8 月 14 日星期一 14:12:06 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Musk vs. Zuckerberg Fight May Never Happen, but Italian Cities Are Still Jostling to Host It]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>科技巨头对决的可能性越来越渺茫，但这并没有阻止古代角斗士故乡的狂热兴奋<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835079/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="罗马斗兽场被认为太脆弱，不适合硅谷首席执行官之间的任何斗争。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>罗马斗兽场被认为太脆弱，不适合硅谷首席执行官之间的任何斗争。阿蒂拉诺·加西亚/祖玛出版社<span>阿蒂拉诺·加西亚/祖玛出版社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132647"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132647"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/eric-sylvers" itemprop="url" rel="author">埃里克·西尔弗斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 9:43 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/musk-vs-zuckerberg-fight-may-never-happen-but-italian-cities-are-still-jostling-to-host-it-36957867"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">埃隆·马斯克</a>和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/mark-zuckerberg">马克·扎克伯格</a>似乎无法就是否以及何时<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-mark-zuckerberg-cage-fight-b71fa4ff?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">进行笼式比赛达成</a>一致。尽管如此，拥有著名考古场所的意大利城市仍在争相成为一场能够带来大规模全球宣传的活动的舞台。</p><p>上周，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSLA" class="">特斯拉</a>首席执行官<span class="company-name-type">马斯克</span>在他的社交媒体公司 X（前身为 Twitter）上发布的帖子在意大利各城市引发了热潮。 “相机画面中的一切都是古罗马的，所以根本没有现代的东西。我与意大利总理和文化部长进行了交谈。他们已经就一个史诗般的地点达成了一致。” <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1689963696703848449" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">马斯克写道</a>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="company-name">Facebook</a>母公司 Meta 的首席执行官扎克伯格<a href="https://www.threads.net/@zuck/post/Cv0Kc-yP2Wu" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">周日在竞争对手平台 Threads 上进行了反击</a>，指责马斯克没有认真参加拳击比赛，并对这场比赛表示怀疑。 “埃隆不会确认日期，然后说他需要手术，现在要求在我的后院进行一轮练习。如果埃隆认真对待一次真正的约会和官方活动，他知道如何联系我。”</p><p>这两位科技亿万富翁在六月份表示，他们将互相争斗。从那以后，他们<a href="https://www.wsj.com/sports/mark-zuckerberg-elon-musk-fight-cage-match-7b28d9c1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">互相互相嘲讽</a>，但很少透露这场比赛的具体细节。</p><p>马斯克提到的古罗马让许多意大利人认为他指的是罗马城而不是帝国。罗马斗兽场显然是角斗比赛的有力竞争者。</p><p>但在意大利官员称公元 80 年竣工的罗马斗兽场过于脆弱之后，这场看似是世界上最知名的古迹之一的首轮淘汰赛很快就变成了一场混战。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=C88AF8C6-9381-4531-8397-8E3466D42127&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fmusk-vs-zuckerberg-fight-may-never-happen-but-italian-cities-are-still-jostling-to-host-it-36957867&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> 《华尔街日报》的乔安娜·斯特恩 (Joanna Stern) 在人物模型的帮助下分析了为什么这场科技争吵实际上就像过去的硅谷争吵一样。照片插图：Kenny Wassus、Preston Jessee<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>意大利文化部长根纳罗·桑朱利亚诺称赞马斯克和扎克伯格的战斗是一场“伟大的事件”，但没有透露可能的地点。该部和意大利总理办公室没有回应置评请求。</p><p>罗马斗兽场退出后，人们的目光转向了马克西穆斯竞技场，这座长椭圆形体育场距离酒店仅几步之遥。</p><p>在古代，马克西穆斯竞技场举办战车比赛，例如好莱坞史诗《宾虚》中描述的比赛。如今，这里偶尔举办摇滚音乐会，有时令当地人懊恼不已。本月早些时候，特拉维斯·斯科特的一场音乐会变得如此喧闹，以至于居民们表示他们以为发生了地震。</p><p>进入舞台右侧：《宾虚》中使用的电影布景，现在是罗马郊区电影主题公园 Cinecittà World 的一部分。该公园的首席执行官称该场地是两全其美，既提供了古老的氛围，又不玷污真正的纪念碑。</p><p>罗马政客们一直在推动<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-ostia-a-search-for-the-secrets-of-romes-port-1454089086?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在古罗马港口奥斯蒂亚安蒂卡（Ostia Antica）</a>建造一个相对较小的剧院，距离城市只有很短的火车车程。</p><p>意大利南部的卡拉布里亚地区也提出了自己的观点，地区主席提醒所有人，该地区是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-riace-bronzes-warriors-rescued-from-the-sea-1464385173?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">里亚斯青铜雕像</a>的故乡，这是两尊古老的裸体战士雕像。别介意这两座巨大的雕像是 50 年前从海底打捞出来的，现在存放在博物馆里，它们起源于希腊，比罗马崛起早了几个世纪。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="468" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835080?width=700&amp;height=468" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">埃隆·马斯克上周表示，这场比赛将在意大利举行。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：贡萨洛·富恩特斯/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>“如果你正在寻找一个史诗般的地方，令人回味和迷人，陶尔米纳就是你的选择，”西西里镇镇长卡特诺·德卢卡 (Cateno De Luca) 在 X.陶尔米纳 (X. Taormina) 上写道，该景点在 HBO 节目中播出后迅速流行起来。 “白莲花”有一个古希腊剧院，可以看到西西里海岸线的全景。</p><p>一份竞争对手的提案来自那不勒斯附近的贝内文托市长，该市有一座罗马剧院，有时被称为罗马斗兽场的双胞胎，另一个提案来自巴西利卡塔南部地区的一个小镇，该镇也有一座罗马剧院。</p><p>庞贝市长提出了在这座被挖掘的古城中使用剧院的理由，这座古城在公元 79 年因维苏威火山爆发而被掩埋。</p><p>维罗纳竞技场是一座保存完好、比罗马斗兽场稍古老的圆形剧场，矗立在不幸恋人罗密欧与朱丽叶的故乡，上演大型歌剧作品。自称“爱之城”的维罗纳市长迄今为止一直保持沉默——也许是因为举办笼斗比赛看起来很尴尬。</p><p>一些意大利人认为，对于一个拥有如此丰富历史和古迹的国家来说，举办亿万富翁之间的打斗是不合适的。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835082?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">罗马马克西穆斯竞技场一直在竞选主办这场比赛的机会。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：格雷戈里奥·博吉亚/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835083?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">西西里小镇陶尔米纳的古希腊剧院最近人气猛增。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：安东尼奥·帕里内洛/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>文化部好斗的副部长维托里奥·斯加尔比(Vittorio Sgarbi)经常介入意大利的文化战争，他表示自己根本不关心这场斗争，也不会观看。他表示，马斯克和扎克伯格可以使用任何潜在的场地，包括罗马斗兽场，只要他们付费。</p><p>斯加尔比说，文化部长桑朱利亚诺已就意大利是否应该主办这次活动征求他的意见。</p><p> “对我来说，这很好，”斯加尔比在接受《晚邮报》采访时回答道。 “他们会给你多少钱？一亿？”</p><p>桑朱利亚诺表示，马斯克和扎克伯格的任何资金都将用于科学研究和升级两家儿科医院。</p><p>斯加尔比表示，他会在这场斗争中支持马斯克，因为特斯拉首席执行官曾在议会演讲中称赞了他。</p><p>另一位反对派议员卡洛·卡伦达 (Carlo Calenda) 在 X 上写道：“我只是觉得令人震惊的是，意大利的文化遗产被提供给了两位想像白痴青少年一样战斗的亿万富翁。”“这不是他们付多少钱的问题。有些东西根本不卖。其中之一就是一个伟大国家的尊严和历史。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835084?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">维罗纳的竞技场是一座保存完好的圆形剧场，比罗马斗兽场稍古老。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Mickael Chavet/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>写信给埃里克·西尔弗斯（Eric Sylvers）： <a href="mailto:eric.sylvers@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">eric.sylvers@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 13:43:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/musk-vs-zuckerberg-fight-may-never-happen-but-italian-cities-are-still-josdling-to-host-it-36957867</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/musk-vs-zuckerberg-fight-may-never-happen-but-italian-cities-are-still-josdling-to-host-it-36957867<author><![CDATA[Eric Sylvers]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>地区政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>马克·扎克伯格</category><category>埃隆·马斯克</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>地区政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Canada Tests the Limits of Its Liberal Immigration Strategy]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>新移民数量迅速增加，给住房、医疗和交通带来压力<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834831/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="加拿大去年迎来了超过一百万永久和临时移民。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>加拿大去年迎来了超过一百万永久和临时移民。大卫·瑞德/路透社<span>大卫·瑞德/路透社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093529"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093529"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/paul-vieira" itemprop="url" rel="author">保罗·维埃拉</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 9:00（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-tests-the-limits-of-its-liberal-immigration-strategy-bc61e0de"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>渥太华——大量移民使加拿大成为近年来增长第二快的发达国家经济体，仅次于美国，因为它竞相<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-woos-american-h-1b-visa-holders-fed-up-with-u-s-immigration-system-5f7e866d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">吸引来自世界各地的高技能工人</a>。</p><p>现在，新来者<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canadas-immigration-problem-not-enough-homes-for-newcomers-11665144002?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">开始限制</a>该国吸收他们的能力，使该国增长的一个重要引擎面临风险。</p><p>加拿大统计局称，这个拥有 4000 万人口的国家去年迎来了超过<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-stretch-of-canadian-border-bustles-with-migrants-1503efb0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">100 万永久和临时移民</a>。人口涌入导致人口增长 2.7%；增加的105万人几乎相当于美国去年的增幅，而美国的人口是加拿大的八倍多。</p><p>加拿大官员表示，未来两年，他们将把永久新移民的数量增加近三分之一，其中大多数是技术移民，如木匠、计算机科学家和医疗保健工作者，他们符合基于绩效的积分制度。</p><p>该体系由总理贾斯汀·特鲁多 (Justin Trudeau) 政府大力提倡，但于 20 世纪 60 年代首次开发，有助于推动经济增长、吸引企业家并填补技术职位空缺。它得到了加拿大政界的广泛支持，其目标是吸引世界上最优秀和最聪明的人才来到加拿大。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825356?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">加拿大的房价仍然位居世界最高之列。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：卡罗莱纳安德拉德/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>但新移民的数量增长如此之快，以至于分析师和新移民表示，这给<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-migration-boom-keeps-housing-costs-high-5fc84b7f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">过热的房地产市场</a>火上浇油，给紧张的医疗系统带来压力，并堵塞了不习惯交通拥堵的城市的道路。</p><p>这也促使移民在选择加拿大时三思而后行。 27 岁的卡兰维尔·辛格 (Karanvir Singh) 来自新德里，是一名训练有素的会计师，在都柏林呆了四年后，于去年 11 月获得工作许可证来到多伦多地区。他说，考虑到房价、食品成本和公共交通的低迷，他正在重新考虑。</p><p>辛格说，加拿大“试图尽可能多地让所有移民来这里经营经济，但他们错过了一个事实，即他们必须建立一个地方，或开发一个地方……这样移民才能在这里生活。”</p><p>达拉斯联邦储备银行编制的数据显示，即使在利率快速大幅上涨之后，该国的房价仍然位居世界最高之列。分析师称，由于住宅建设跟不上人口增长，加拿大房价比 2020 年水平高出 36%。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="479" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825693?width=639&amp;height=479" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">卡兰维尔·辛格 (Karanvir Singh) 是一名训练有素的会计师，去年 11 月抵达多伦多地区，他表示，他正在重新考虑是否留下来。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：卡兰维尔·辛格</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>约翰·帕萨利斯说：“当我们的政府决定将人口增长速度提高两倍而不考虑每个人的居住地点时，就会发生这种情况。”</p>多伦多房地产经纪公司 Realosophy Realty 总裁。<p></p><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TD" class="company-name">道明银行</a>经济学家在上个月的一份报告中预测，根据当前的人口趋势，满足预期需求所需的住房单位缺口可能会在短短两年内翻一番，达到 50 万套。</p><p> Aurika Tabassum 于 2014 年持学生签证从孟加拉国来到这里，学习人力资源管理。她现在在多伦多结婚，在一家招聘公司工作，并于六月得知加拿大授予她永久居留权。但她和她的丈夫买不起房，他们在多伦多北部租的公寓——两间卧室，这样亲戚从国外来访时可以留下来——花费了他们一半以上的税前工资，她说。</p><p> Tabassum 说，在美国的某些地区，“你可以花 30 万或 40 万美元购买一栋大房子。在这里，你连地下室都买不了。”塔巴苏姆说，她现在警告热衷于在这里定居的孟加拉国朋友和亲戚有关住房成本的问题。</p><p>加拿大以欢迎移民而闻名，并没有经历美国和荷兰等国家最近出现的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/immigration-backlashes-spread-around-the-world-142124bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">强烈抵制</a>。但渥太华 Abacus Data 上个月发布的新民意调查反映出了质疑，61% 的公民表示，政府的计划过于雄心勃勃，因为这对住房和医疗保健产生了负面影响。加拿大医学协会表示，该国的人口与医生比例在 36 个发达经济体中排名第 29 位，而经济合作与发展组织的数据显示，加拿大的医院床位容量是人均最低的国家之一跻身于富裕世界经济体之列。</p><p> “任何时候增加人口，尤其是在医疗资源紧张的环境下，都会产生影响，”加拿大医学协会主席阿利卡·拉方丹博士说。</p><p>以特鲁多为首的加拿大政府官员捍卫了该国的政策。直到上个月末仍担任加拿大移民部长的肖恩·弗雷泽 (Sean Fraser) 表示，来自海外的新工人的增加帮助该国从<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-looks-to-immigration-to-boost-economic-recovery-11617105739?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">疫情的经济深渊</a>中恢复过来。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="503" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834830?width=700&amp;height=503" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">以总理贾斯汀·特鲁多为首的加拿大政府官员为该国的移民政策辩护。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Adrian Wyld/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>弗雷泽在 6 月份回答问题的电子邮件中表示，新移民发挥了关键作用，“通过新想法、创新和庞大的数量来补充加拿大人才库，以帮助解决严重的劳动力短缺问题”。他说，加拿大正在让技术熟练的商人和护士更容易在该国定居，并补充说这将有助于缓解住房建设和医疗保健方面的紧缩。</p><p>加拿大央行行长蒂夫·麦克勒姆(Tiff Macklem)上个月在新闻发布会上表示，移民帮助劳动力市场降温，这是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-inflation-cools-in-may-as-gasoline-prices-drop-aa65ec96?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">通胀降至</a>央行2%目标的先决条件。该国失业率连续三个月攀升，7 月份为 5.5%，此前在 2023 年大部分时间里一直保持在 5.0% 的历史低点附近。</p><p> “另一方面，”麦克勒姆说，“这些新移民，他们也是新消费者，他们是新租房者，他们是新购房者，所以他们也增加了需求。”加拿大央行在过去16个月内<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bank-of-canada-lifts-interest-rates-warns-path-to-stable-inflation-at-risk-18462fb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">加息</a>10次，累计加息4.75个百分点，以抑制消费者支出、减缓通胀。</p><p>从历史上看，新移民涌向多伦多、温哥华和蒙特利尔等大城市，但现在他们也在较小的城市和郊区定居。</p><p>根据全国人口普查，加拿大首都渥太华周边地区的总人口在 2016 年至 2021 年间增长了 8.5%，根据加拿大房地产协会的数据，同期房价飙升了 84%。位于多伦多以西 70 英里的基奇纳-滑铁卢-剑桥地区是一个技术和制造中心，人口增长了 10%，达到 575,000 人。 2016-21年期间，房价上涨了一倍多。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825439?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">移民正在大城市以外的小城镇定居，例如位于多伦多以北约 33 英里的布拉德福德西格威廉伯里 (Bradford West Gwillimbury)。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：科尔·伯斯顿/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>随着移民激增，加拿大的人均国内生产总值（经济学家广泛用来衡量一个国家的生活水平）已经下降。国家银行金融上个月表示，加拿大第二季度人均产出有望同比下降1.7%，经济合作与发展组织预测加拿大人均GDP增速可能是最低的之一未来四十年中发达国家经济体的发展。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>美国应该效仿加拿大的移民策略吗？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>加拿大激进的移民“掩盖了这个国家真正的根本问题，即缺乏商业投资和生产力，”美林前首席北美经济学家、现任罗森博格研究中心负责人戴维·罗森伯格说。他说，这体现在公共交通、道路、医疗保健和住房等各个方面。</p><p>戴尔·雷诺特 (Dale Renout) 是安大略省布兰特福德罗登街浸信会教堂 (Rawdon Street Baptist Church) 的牧师，该教堂的人口比五年前增长了 6.2%。雷诺特表示，他支持移民，但认为现在是加拿大限制新移民数量的时候了，根据他的经验，他试图帮助新移民找到负担得起的租金，但基本上没有成功。他还指出布兰特福德出现了交通拥堵的情况。</p><p> “医院床位没有增加，道路通行能力也没有增加，”雷诺特说。 “我只是不知道新移民要去哪里。”</p><p>写信给保罗·维埃拉 (Paul Vieira)： <a href="mailto:Paul.Vieira@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Paul.Vieira@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 13:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-tests-the-limits-of-its-liberal-immigration-strategy-bc61e0de</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-tests-the-limits-of-its-liberal-immigration-strategy-bc61e0de<author><![CDATA[Paul Vieira]]></author><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>房地产市场</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>人类迁徙</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>房地产市场</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>人类迁徙</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Taiwan Vice President Flashes Defiance Against China During U.S. Stopover]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>赖清德访美期间在纽约发表讲话，北京和华盛顿都在密切关注<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132434"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="484" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835016?width=860&amp;height=484" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">台湾副总统赖清德周日出席了在曼哈顿宴会厅举行的午餐会。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：台湾总统府/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132434"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joyu-wang" itemprop="url" rel="author">Joyu Wang</a></span> （台北）和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/james-t-areddy" itemprop="url" rel="author">James T. Areddy</a></span> （纽约）</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 8:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-vice-president-flashes-defiance-against-china-during-u-s-stopover-e3596b74"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>台湾副总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-visit-by-taiwan-vice-president-puts-china-in-a-bind-a275b893?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在纽约短暂停留</a>期间，誓言不会在面对来自中国的威胁时让步，这是美国访问的一部分，北京和华盛顿似乎都保持克制，以<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-taiwan-relations-tensions-explained-11653322751?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">避免重新引发紧张局势</a>。</p><p>赖清德在曼哈顿逗留了大约 24 小时，并于前一天晚上抵达曼哈顿的一个宴会厅，在有 500 多人参加的周日午宴上发表讲话。他在河边遇到了一群喧闹的亲北京抗议者，他进入后就散去。</p><p> “在这个关键时刻，我希望此时此地，我们能够再次重申我们的承诺，无论威权主义对台湾的威胁有多大，我们都不会畏惧和退缩，”赖说。他还感谢美国政府“不屈服于压力”帮助安排他在美国的停留，这间接提到了北京。</p><p>目前在定于一月举行的总统选举中领先的赖智正在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-unveils-dates-for-u-s-stops-by-vice-president-despite-chinas-protests-17106008?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">巴拉圭进行为期一周的访问</a>，他计划周二出席该国即将上任的总统圣地亚哥·佩尼亚·帕拉西奥斯的就职典礼。他计划周三在旧金山停留，然后第二天返回台北。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwans-vice-president-plans-stop-in-the-u-s-at-a-delicate-moment-886e484b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">台湾官员过境</a>美国被正式称为过境，这符合华盛顿数十年来向北京做出的不与这个民主自治岛屿保持正式外交关系的承诺。北京将台湾视为中国的一部分，一再警告美国不要允许黎智英在中途停留时离开机场。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=056CAD44-242B-4B81-BC61-72E5DF1CD69A&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ftaiwan-vice-president-flashes-defiance-against-china-during-u-s-stopover-e3596b74&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">几十年来，台湾一直将其东海岸视为在中国入侵时幸存下来的避风港，直到盟友，特别是美国能够到达提供援助。但解放军在该岛东部的活动使这一战略受到质疑。插图：亚当·阿达达<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>周日，黎智英冒险进入纽约后，中国驻纽约领事馆提出抗议，他一度受到一群挥舞旗帜、唱着歌的支持者的欢迎。</p><p> “赖清德是不折不扣的‘台独’分裂分子，”领事馆在一份声明中表示。 “他‘过境’美国的目的是为台湾选举造势，寻求美国对‘台独’的支持”</p><p>赖清德和台湾总统蔡英文都是台湾执政党民进党的党员，但华盛顿和北京都认为赖清德在主张台湾独立方面更加激进——这是中国领导层的红线，中国誓言要控制台湾。必要时使用武力自治岛屿。</p><p>赖表示，如果当选，他将维持与中国的现状。</p><p>尽管如此，美国和台湾官员仍决定低调访问美国，除负责台湾政策的官员外，没有计划与美国官员会面。</p><p>到目前为止，北京方面同样谨慎行事，仅限于口头反应，甚至减少了对台湾附近空域和水域的日常军事入侵。台湾官员和军事分析人士表示，中国可能对采取可能有助于赖以民意调查的挑衅行动持谨慎态度。</p><p>在黎智英出访前几天，中国喷气式战斗机、轰炸机和其他军用飞机每日出动架次超过 30 架次，但台湾国防部表示，周末仅发现 13 架中国战机靠近其领空。报告称，自黎智英周六离开以来，没有人跨越过台湾海峡的中线，这条100英里长的水域将台湾与中国分开。</p><p>在黎智英在周日午餐会上被介绍上台之前，组织者欢迎一些地区政界人士出席活动，其中包括来自纽约、新泽西和宾夕法尼亚州的一些州议员。</p><p>美国在台协会常务董事英格丽德·拉尔森 (Ingrid Larson) 简短致辞，对赖清德表示欢迎。美国在台协会事实上的美国驻台湾大使馆的负责人劳拉·罗森伯格(Laura Rosenberger)通过视频发表讲话，并表示，她期待着黎智英在巴拉圭访问结束后返回美国，并在旧金山欢迎他。</p><p>赖清德利用他的讲话来强化台湾作为对抗中国在亚太地区威权野心的民主堡垒的形象。</p><p>他说：“我们必须勇敢、坚定地走在民主道路上，继续壮大台湾。” “尽管国际形势复杂，但我会以和平为指路明灯。” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/bf4d14ac-311a-4b61-9cc1-ce0772d8de02.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>写信给 Joyu Wang（ <a href="mailto:joyu.wang@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">joyu.wang@wsj.com）</a>和 James T. Areddy（ <a href="mailto:James.Areddy@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">James.Areddy@wsj.com）</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 12:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-vice-president-flashes-defiance-against-china-during-us-stopover-e3596b74</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-vice-president-flashes-defiance-against-china-during-us-stopover-e3596b74<author><![CDATA[Joyu WangJames T. Areddy]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>赖清德</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kim Jong Un Calls for Sharp Rise in North Korean Weapons Production]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>美国和韩国定于下周开始大型军事演习，平壤称之为战争预演<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132369"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835000?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">朝鲜领导人金正恩在参观军工厂时检查一辆装甲车。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：朝中社 VIA KNS/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132369"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dasl-yoon" itemprop="url" rel="author">达斯尔·尹</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 7:01 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-north-korea-weapons-production-e5d0f509"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>首尔——随着美国和韩国加强军事合作以对抗朝鲜，朝鲜领导人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/kim-jong-un">金正恩</a>呼吁大幅增加武器生产。</p><p>据平壤官方媒体周一报道，这是金正恩<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-spotlights-weapons-amid-u-s-concerns-about-illegal-arms-trade-3375283c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">几周内第二次</a>参观军事工厂，这一次是在周五和周六观察战术导弹、移动发射平台和炮弹的制造。据官方媒体报道，他下令增加为前线部队生产炮弹，“为应对任何时刻的战争做好充分准备”。</p><p>最近几周，朝鲜对其武器生产和军事实力越来越直言不讳。据官方媒体报道，金正恩上周召集军方官员讨论针对韩国的“重大军事行动”，并在会上呼吁“做好战争充分准备”，但该媒体没有详细说明。</p><p>美国和韩国定于下周开始大型军事演习，朝鲜通常将其称为入侵预演。据首尔军方称，今年的一年一度的乙支自由之盾演习<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-south-korea-revive-live-military-drills-after-four-year-hiatus-11661074202?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">——去年以实景演习形式恢复</a>——将是有史以来规模最大的一次，将有数万名士兵以及联合国军司令部成员国参加。</p><p> “这些演习对于应对朝鲜日益增长的军事威胁是绝对必要的，”韩国参谋长联席会议发言人李成俊在周一的新闻发布会上表示。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=901F4C0B-AEB7-4EE0-90AB-3AAD0B945CAA&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fkim-jong-un-north-korea-weapons-production-e5d0f509&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">朝鲜媒体显示，领导人金正恩带着俄罗斯国防部长谢尔盖·绍伊古参观了一个装满武器的大厅，包括导弹和无人机。此次活动正值俄罗斯和中国代表团访问该国庆祝朝鲜战争结束 70 周年。照片：法新社照片/朝中社 VIA KNS<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>朝鲜今年举行了大规模阅兵活动<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korean-parade-puts-missile-production-prowess-on-display-11675937910?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">，纪念其武装部队成立 75 周年</a>，以及结束 1950-53 年朝鲜战争停战协定签署 70 周年，朝鲜将这一天称为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-celebrates-major-holiday-with-special-guests-from-china-and-russia-fc3386fc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">“胜利日”。</a></p><p> 9月9日，纪念共和国成立75周年，将举行民兵阅兵，这可能意味着士兵们走过，而不是武器滚过。</p><p>纪念五周年或十年周年纪念日是夸耀该政权经济和军事成就的机会。但梨花女子大学朝鲜研究教授朴元建表示，制裁和平壤自行关闭边境的影响迫使金正恩强调军队。</p><p> “金正恩越来越频繁地出现在与军事相关的活动和设施中，这表明他没有可以宣传的经济成就，这表明经济正在陷入困境，”朴说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="464" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834999?width=700&amp;height=464" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">朝鲜周一发布了一张未注明日期的照片，显示金正恩正在参观一家军火工厂。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：朝中社/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>官方媒体照片显示，金正恩身穿白色夹克，驾驶新型通用战斗装甲车，检查正在生产的短程导弹。自<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-north-koreas-kim-end-nuclear-summit-early-11551334804?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">2019 年与美国的谈判破裂</a>以来，朝鲜继续扩大其导弹和核计划。自去年以来，平壤已发射了 100 多枚导弹，其中包括测试新型<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-fires-ballistic-missile-toward-japan-2c728f14?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">固体燃料洲际弹道导弹，</a>并在上个月的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-flaunts-north-koreas-newest-weapons-with-russia-and-china-by-his-side-125399f5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">胜利日阅兵</a>中展示了新型攻击无人机。</p><p>随着华盛顿在朝鲜半岛<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-nuclear-capable-boomer-sub-visits-south-korea-for-first-time-in-decades-dc4a8187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">部署更多战略资产</a>并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/south-korea-u-s-military-drills-could-use-nuclear-assets-president-yoon-suk-yeol-says-11672669292?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">扩大</a>与韩国的军事演习，金氏政权将其军事建设视为防御性的。</p><p> “乙支自由之盾”演习是一项计算机模拟的指挥所演习，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/south-korean-president-to-visit-pyongyang-in-bid-to-revive-diplomacy-1537136720?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">寻求与朝鲜进行外交努力的</a>韩国前总统文在寅领导下，演习规模被缩减了四年。今年的演习包括30场大型实战训练活动，而去年为13场。据驻韩美军称，美国太空军也将与美国陆军、空军和海军陆战队人员一起参加今年的联合演习。</p><p>本月早些时候， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-spotlights-weapons-amid-u-s-concerns-about-illegal-arms-trade-3375283c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">金正恩参观了五家武器工厂</a>，检查巡航导弹和无人机发动机的生产情况。时任俄罗斯国防部长谢尔盖·绍伊古</p>金正恩上个月访问平壤参加大规模的胜利日阅兵式时，带他参观了展示朝鲜导弹、发射车和无人机的国防展览。<p></p><p>美国官员表示，随着乌克兰战争的持续，俄罗斯正<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-is-again-turning-to-north-korea-to-replenish-ammunition-supplies-d79a5318?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">寻求从朝鲜购买更多弹药</a>以补充供应。莫斯科和平壤一再誓言要在战争期间加强合作，但否认有任何武器交易。联合国安理会已禁止朝鲜测试导弹或出售武器。</p><p>本周五，拜登总统计划在戴维营接待韩国总统尹锡烈和日本首相岸田文雄，三位领导人将<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-first-camp-david-summit-looks-to-align-allies-facing-china-threat-89626785?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">在那里宣布两国将每年举行联合军事演习</a>。美国及其盟国正在整合雷达、卫星和武器系统，以应对朝鲜的核威胁和导弹威胁。</p><p>写信给 Dasl Yoon，邮箱为<a href="mailto:dasl.yoon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dasl.yoon@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 11:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-north-korea-weapons-product-e5d0f509</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/kim-jong-un-north-korea-weapons-product-e5d0f509<author><![CDATA[Dasl Yoon]]></author><category>航空航天/国防</category><category>工业品</category><category>输出/生产</category><category>新产品/服务</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>产品与服务</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>武器计划</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>金正恩</category><category>输出</category><category>生产</category><category>新产品</category><category>服务</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>产品</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>武器计划</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>航天</category><category>防御</category><category>工业品</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ozempic Settles the Obesity Debate: It’s Biology Over Willpower]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>减肥药物影响大脑的方式有助于研究人员了解身体如何调节体重<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834611/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>埃米尔·伦多夫/华尔街日报<span>埃米尔·伦多夫/华尔街日报</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129880"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129880"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/betsy-mckay" itemprop="url" rel="author">贝特西·麦凯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/weight-loss-drugs-obesity-e4bb2173"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> Ozempic 和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-drugs-that-are-gaining-on-ozempic-71cdeb51?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">类似药物</a>正在改变世界<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-wegovy-weight-loss-body-positivity-marketing-6e918f8c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对肥胖的认识</a>。这与意志力无关<strong>：</strong>而是与生物学有关。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-diabetes-drug-weight-loss-c0e03c25?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">强大的新型</a>糖尿病和减肥药物的成功表明化学对于确定一个人的体重有多么重要。大脑是人体的首席化学家，负责调节食欲，使许多人难以减肥并保持体重。根据<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mounjaro-eli-lilly-weight-loss-new-study-5f7661cc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">新药支持的</a>多年研究，大脑决定了它希望人们携带多少脂肪。</p><p>这个量就像表盘上的设置，或者许多研究人员所说的“设定点”或“防御脂肪量”。大脑通过调节一个人的饮食量来维持刻度设置或设定点。一些肥胖研究人员表示，Ozempic、它的姊妹药物 Wegovy <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-mounjaro-weight-loss-drug-wegovy-eli-lilly-66f2906?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">和另一种药物 Mounjaro</a>可以降低刻度盘设置或设定点，通过作用于大脑来减少饥饿感并让人更快感到饱足<strong>。</strong></p><p>他们说，只要患者<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-wegovy-stop-weight-loss-ea925ae1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">服用药物</a>，新的设定点就会持续存在。在开始服用其中一种药物之前吃得很多的患者<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-weight-loss-drugs-strains-relationships-327ab217?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">会感觉不那么饥饿</a>，并且很快就会有饱腹感——有时在吃完一片披萨后，他们曾经吃掉了整个披萨。</p><p> “这与意志力或个人选择无关，”虚拟医疗减肥诊所 Form 的内分泌学家兼首席医疗官弗洛伦西亚·哈尔珀林 (Florencia Halperin) 博士说。 “这与你的大脑驱动行为有关。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=35CD7B9E-3215-4417-9DEE-8FF9D9BBEDC9&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fweight-loss-drugs-obesity-e4bb2173&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">糖尿病药物可能成为治疗行为问题和成瘾的有效方法。 《华尔街日报》的丹妮拉·埃尔南德斯 (Daniela Hernandez) 详细剖析了它们的工作原理以及它们如何永远改变精神病学。图片插图：伊丽莎白·斯梅洛夫<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pediatricians-recommend-weight-loss-drugs-for-obese-children-11673213563?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与肥胖的斗争</a>中，这些药物及其对生物学的见解已经到了一个岌岌可危的地步。尽管美国人每年花费数十亿美元来减肥， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/more-states-show-prevalence-of-obesity-cdc-finds-11631734589?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">但超重的人数却在</a>不断增加。根据该机构的数据，近 42% 的美国成年人患有肥胖症<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/obesity/data/adult.html" target="_blank" class="icon none">&nbsp;</a>最新的<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/obesity/data/adult.html" target="_blank" class="icon none">政府统计数据</a>，比 1999 年的 31% 有所上升<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/obesity/data/childhood.html" target="_blank" class="icon none">。五分之一</a>也是如此<strong>&nbsp;</strong>孩子们。</p><p>肥胖者更容易<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/after-decades-of-progress-america-backslides-on-heart-disease-11561129106?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">患心脏病</a>、中风和糖尿病。治疗它们<a href="https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0247307#pone.0247307.ref002" target="_blank" class="icon none">每年花费</a>超过 1700 亿美元。 Wegovy 已被证明可以<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/wegovy-weight-loss-drug-heart-attack-stroke-570f435e?mod=hp_lead_pos6&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">降低心血管风险</a>，而 Mounjaro 正在研究其是否具有额外的健康益处。</p><p>新药打破了一些长期以来关于体重和健康的假设。 “这些药物已经证明，患者是对的：这不是他们的错，”肥胖治疗专家、威尔康奈尔医学院代谢研究教授路易斯·阿龙博士说。</p><p>他和许多其他研究肥胖或开新药的专家为生产这些药物的公司提供建议或进行研究。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834335?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Ozempic 注射笔是一种新型药物，颠覆了人们长期以来对体重的假设。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Jaap Arriens/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乔恩·韦斯曼</p>2020 年，当他寻求减肥帮助时，体重约为 300 磅，处于糖尿病前期，有患心脏病的风险。这位 46 岁的人在波士顿从事抵押贷款银行和房地产工作，曾尝试限制食物，但总是感到更饿。 “我每天无法摄入 2,000 卡路里热量，”他说。 “我大概收到了 4,000 美元。”<p></p><p>他重新开始使用他之前尝试过的上一代减肥药 Saxenda。他减掉了大约 30 磅，但随后就达到了稳定状态。</p><p> 2021 年 9 月，他与 Halperin 医生商议，后者<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-you-cant-find-wegovy-the-weight-loss-drug-11670108199?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">开了 Wegovy。</a>他的饥饿感很快就减轻了。他不再渴望洋葱圈、通心粉和奶酪以及其他他曾经在与朋友的马拉松晚餐中吃过的重口味食物，现在更喜欢绿色和蛋白质。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="639" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834317?width=639&amp;height=639" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乔恩·韦斯曼 (Jon Weisman) 正在服用 Wegovy。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔恩·韦斯曼</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>几个月前，他的体重达到了 180 磅的目标，目前仍在继续服用该药物，有时他需要打电话到几家药店才能找到药物。 “这是我余生都必须接受的治疗，”他说。他停止了服用的两种降压药物，改用低剂量的降胆固醇药物，并且不再处于糖尿病前期。他现在吃得更多了，是为了维持体重而不是减肥。</p><p>肥胖症的流行是新旧力量相互碰撞的产物，这些力量在像韦斯曼这样的人身上发生了碰撞：人类生物学在数千年的寻找生计的斗争中形成；大部分时间都是坐着的生活；以及<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cake-could-be-the-secret-to-teaching-kids-about-healthy-eating-habits-c4947362?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">大量廉价的加工食品</a>。</p><p>研究表明，薯片、苏打水和其他廉价加工食品是罪魁祸首，因为它们的热量、糖、盐和脂肪含量很高，而且<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-end-of-craving-review-why-you-cant-eat-just-one-11635977800?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">让人难以放下</a>。 People who lived for a month in a research facility at the National Institutes of Health ate more and <a href="https://www.cell.com/cell-metabolism/fulltext/S1550-4131(19)30248-7" target="_blank" class="icon none">gained weight</a> on a diet of processed meats and cheeses, tater tots and other processed foods compared with when they were on a diet of vegetables, whole grains, fish and other unprocessed foods, according to a 2019 study.</p><p> For some people, high-calorie foods are especially problematic.</p><p> At least 1,500 genes are linked with weight. Some people are genetically predisposed to gain weight, depending on the combinations of variants in those genes, said Ruth Loos, a professor focused on the genetics of obesity at the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NVO" class="company-name">Novo Nordisk</a> Foundation Center for Metabolic Research at the University of Copenhagen and at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai. These genes often act in the brain.</p><p> Primitive parts of the brain that control breathing, heartbeat and other essential functions collaborate with hormones and the central nervous system to determine how much fat the body wants to have and keep it at the set point. The system has been shaped by thousands of years of humans foraging to survive.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>How have Ozempic and other weight-loss drugs changed your understanding of obesity?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> The brain sends hunger signals when a person needs fuel to reach or maintain their set point, and signals a sense of fullness when they reach or exceed it. That is why people who lose weight fighting off an illness are ravenous once they recover, or why people <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/can-ozempic-treat-binge-eating-for-some-the-answer-is-yes-dbdc009f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">feel sick when they overeat</a> . It&#39;s also why people— <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4989512/" target="_blank" class="icon none">like some participants</a> in “The Biggest Loser” TV series—tend to regain weight even after they try to lose it, according to research.</p><p> The set point isn&#39;t set: It changes naturally throughout a person&#39;s lifetime. Babies lose body fat. Women gain weight during pregnancy <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-if-we-could-get-rid-of-menopause-7adbc4e0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">and menopause</a> . It can make small changes, with a person gaining or losing a few pounds.</p><p> In a person with obesity, however, the set-point system has gotten out of whack <strong>,</strong> said Dr. Lee Kaplan, director of the Obesity and Metabolism Institute in Boston. The body-fat dial moves to a new higher set point.</p><p> Obesity causes overeating, rather than the other way around, Kaplan said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834339?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Scientists increasingly see the obesity epidemic as arising from the confluence of abundant high-calorie processed foods, sedentary lifestyles and human biology.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Chona Kasinger/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The new drugs are based on a hormone <strong>&nbsp;</strong> called <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-diabetes-drug-weight-loss-c0e03c25?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">glucagon-like peptide 1</a> , or GLP-1, secreted primarily in the lining of the gut in response to food, and in the brain. Drug hunters were initially interested in GLP-1 because it plays an important role in regulating blood sugar. The first GLP-1 drugs were approved to treat diabetes in 2005.</p><p> Wegovy is the only GLP-1 drug approved by the Food and Drug Administration <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/employers-cut-off-access-to-weight-loss-drugs-for-workers-cb277a44?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">as an anti-obesity treatment</a> , while Ozempic, with a lower dose of the same active ingredient, semaglutide, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-runs-low-for-diabetes-patients-as-weight-loss-use-surges-286bf21a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">is approved for diabetes</a> . The FDA is expected soon to approve Mounjaro for weight loss. Mounjaro, already cleared to treat Type 2 diabetes, mimics the action of a hormone called GIP in addition to GLP-1.</p><p> The medications essentially lower the set point by activating GLP-1 receptors in the hypothalamus and brain stem that regulate weight and appetite, said Randy Seeley, a professor of surgery and director of the Michigan Nutrition Obesity Research Center at the University of Michigan. The drugs also indirectly reach neurons in parts of the brain involved in reward sensations and impulse control.</p><p> “We are in a constant search to identify the most critical neurons that respond to these drugs,” he said.</p><p> Once a patient reaches a new set point, some of their appetite returns—they are no longer feeling overfed—but the medications keep them at their new level, Seeley said. If a patient stops taking the medication, the new set point no longer holds, which is why people regain weight, he said.</p><p> The set point concept is hard to prove definitively, some researchers say. The makers of the drugs, Novo Nordisk and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/LLY" class="">Eli Lilly</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> say their drugs reduce hunger and increase satiety while a person takes them.</p><p> Researchers want to figure out what makes the set point go way up for some people, leading to obesity, Kaplan said: “For the moment, it&#39;s a black box.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/11004b12-051f-4044-aa8a-823e293913dd.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Write to Betsy McKay at <a href="mailto:betsy.mckay@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">betsy.mckay@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/weight-loss-drugs-obesity-e4bb2173</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/weight-loss-drugs-obesity-e4bb2173<author><![CDATA[Betsy McKay]]></author><category> wsjhealth</category><category>药品</category><category>Scientific Research Services</category><category> Healthcare/Life Sciences</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>Specialized Drugs/Medications</category><category> Hormone Products</category><category> Diabetes Drugs</category><category> Medical Research Services</category><category> Drug Discovery/Development</category><category> Healthcare Support Services</category><category> Diagnostic/Medical Research Services</category><category> Biology</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Chemistry</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>健康</category><category>Medical Conditions</category><category>肥胖</category><category>科学/人文</category><category>社会问题</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>生物学</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>化学</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>health</category><category> medical conditions</category><category>肥胖</category><category>科学</category><category>人文学科</category><category>社会问题</category><category>pharmaceuticals</category><category> scientific research services</category><category>卫生保健</category><category>life sciences</category><category> business</category><category>消费服务</category><category>specialized drugs</category><category>药物</category><category>hormone products</category><category> diabetes drugs</category><category> medical research services</category><category> drug discovery</category><category>发展</category><category>healthcare support services</category><category> diagnostic </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Argentines Back Far-Right Outsider in Presidential Primary]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Javier Milei has pledged to dissolve central bank, slash spending in a country hammered by inflation, poverty and a moribund economy <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132138"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834985?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Far-right congressman, Javier Milei, capitalized on anger against the political class to win the most votes in Argentina&#39;s primary election.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: alejandro pagni/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132138"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ryan-dube" itemprop="url" rel="author">瑞安·杜贝</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">Aug. 14, 2023 12:25 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/argentine-presidential-primary-voters-propel-far-right-outsider-to-surprise-win-ec24e5b4"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Javier Milei, a far-right outsider in Argentina who has pledged to close ministries and slash spending if elected president, rocked the political establishment Sunday by beating out conservatives and the ruling Peronist coalition in a primary vote ahead of October&#39;s elections.</p><p> With more than 80% of ballots counted, Milei, a congressman who says he would dollarize Argentina&#39;s economy and dissolve the central bank, had 31% of the vote as he capitalized on anger against the political class. The country of 46 million people is living through its <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/argentina-s-president-names-sergio-massa-as-new-economy-minister-11659044057?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">worst economic crisis</a> in a generation, hobbled by inflation at 116%. Four of every 10 Argentines live in poverty, struggling to survive with a currency that is increasingly worthless.</p><p> “If we don&#39;t change today, the only destiny will be to turn into the biggest slum in the world,” Milei said to his supporters in his closing campaign rally on Aug. 7. “I don&#39;t want your vote so you give me the power, but to give you back your freedom so you can be the architects of your own destiny and we can end this state that makes us poor, with inflation and crime, and put the country on the path to growth.”</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Milei, a long-haired, 52-year-old economist, rails against the ruling class in interviews and darts across the stage in speeches, promising to wash away both institutions and the politicians who are in office. He calls himself an anarcho-capitalist who would slash spending, cut taxes and end a bloated state.</p><p> “If the central bank emits money, it causes damage, if they move to control money, they cause damage,” he told The Wall Street Journal in an interview last year. “不造成损害的唯一方法就是什么都不做，那我为什么要它们呢？ I&#39;d close it because it&#39;s a risk if it&#39;s operating.”</p><p> Milei stunned pollsters by receiving more votes than the traditional political coalitions on the left and right that have governed in recent years and failed to solve Argentina&#39;s grinding economic problems.</p><p> “There is a generalized sense of disbelief at how well he did,” said Nicolás Saldias, an analyst at the Economist Intelligence Unit who closely tracks Argentina. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834988?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Patricia Bullrich, the center-right coalition candidate, in Buenos Aires on Sunday night.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: AGUSTIN MARCARIAN/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The center-right opposition coalition, Together for Change, received about 28% support.周日，选民们选择犯罪严厉的保守派人士、前安全部长帕特里夏·布尔里奇(Patricia Bullrich)作为十月选举中联盟的候选人，这是阿根廷人选举下一任领导人的两轮选举中的第一轮。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/argentinas-ruling-peronists-await-defeat-in-sunday-primary-fa5d99ef?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">The ruling Peronists</a> , which have governed Argentina for most of the last 75 years, received 26.69% support.该运动的候选人将是经济部长塞尔吉奥·马萨，他被认为比总统阿尔贝托·费尔南德斯和副总统克里斯蒂娜·基什内尔更加中间派和对商业友好。</p><p></p><p> Milei attracted young voters in the poor barrios around cities such as Buenos Aires who are angered over the lack of jobs and constantly rising prices for food and clothes. Argentina has been unable to tame inflation and stop the peso currency&#39;s fast depreciation after <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/argentina-imf-reach-deal-to-restructure-bailout-11643379805?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">taking on a $44 billion bailout</a> from the International Monetary Fund in 2018 to avoid a currency crisis.</p><p> “I voted for Milei because, like a majority of Argentines, I am tired of the same so I opted for resounding change,” said Aldana Gómez, an out-of-work office cleaner who calls herself “another of the unemployed majority.”</p><p> “I simply expect a change,” said the 22-year-old Gómez, who lives with her parents in a working-class district outside the capital. She said past governments “had their opportunity and that&#39;s why the country is like it is—a disaster.”</p><p> Asked why he voted for the upstart Milei, César Vargas, a businessman, said: “It&#39;s simple.我厌倦了被欺骗。”他说，近年来阿根廷人的生活变得更加糟糕。 “I&#39;m hoping for a more just Argentina, in the short-term, like the Chilean or Uruguayan model,” he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=FDB4DFD7-9FD4-49A6-9874-2C3D318261D2&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fargentine-presidential-primary-voters-propel-far-right-outsider-to-surprise-win-ec24e5b4&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Brazil&#39;s and Argentina&#39;s leaders have revived the idea of a common currency in a bid to boost trade and reduce the region&#39;s reliance on the US dollar. WSJ&#39;s Samantha Pearson explains why it is unlikely to be implemented anytime soon. Photo: Eve Hartley<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>The results Sunday raise uncertainty for Argentina&#39;s political system, which, despite the country&#39;s economic upheaval, had been relatively stable in recent years while its neighbors were battered by social unrest and the rise of political outsiders.</p><p> “Argentina is famous for its economic chaos, but to some degree earned this reputation as having a fairly predictable political system, and that&#39;s no longer the case,” said Benjamin Gedan, an Argentina expert and director of the Latin America program at the Wilson Center.</p><p> Milei was able to tap Argentine anger though polls show that many voters don&#39;t necessarily agree with his policy proposals, which include eliminating public education, creating a market for selling organs, expanding gun ownership and outlawing abortion.</p><p> “The reality is that he channels the almost-universal anger in Argentina right now,” said Gedan. “And it has nothing to do with his policies.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834896?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Workers in Argentina preparing a polling station. The results of the primary election raise uncertainty for the country&#39;s political system.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Erica Canepa/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Milei faces an uphill battle to become president.民意调查机构称，他十月份的主要竞争对手似乎是布尔里奇。分析人士称，她可能会在大选中吸引许多保守派和中间派选民，他们担心米莱会在颠覆国家政治和经济体系方面走得太远。</p><p> Milei could also face pushback from investors who would be concerned about his ability to govern and pass overhauls needed to curb public spending and bring inflation down.米莱可能很难在反对派控制的国会中通过立法。</p><p> And on the streets of Buenos Aires and other cities, he would face robust opposition from powerful unions and social movements who are quick to protest.</p><p> “If reforms are not carried out cautiously, you could have enormous social upheaval,” said Gedan. “投资者对 Milei 有很多不安。现实是市场不喜欢不确定性。”</p><p> If no candidate wins outright in October, the top two candidates will go to a runoff in November. A second-round vote without a leftist, Peronist candidate, as analysts expect, would be unheard of in Argentina.</p><p> “A runoff between Milei and Bullrich would be unprecedented,” said Sergio Berensztein, a pollster in Buenos Aires. “这是一次反对通货膨胀的投票，一切照旧。”</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Silvina Frydlewsky and Juan Forero contributed to this article.</p><p>写信给 Ryan Dubé： <a href="mailto:ryan.dube@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ryan.dube@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 04:25:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/argentine-presidential-primary-voters-propel-far-right-outsider-to-surprise-win-ec24e5b4</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/argentine-presidential-primary-voters-propel-far-right-outsider-to-surprise-win-ec24e5b4<author><![CDATA[Ryan Dubé]]></author><category> wsjworld</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>Poverty</category><category>社会问题</category><category>Elections</category><category> National/Presidential Elections</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Patricia Bullrich</category><category> Javier Milei</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贫困</category><category>社会问题</category><category>选举</category><category>national</category><category> presidential elections </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Economic Losers in the New World Order]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>巨额补贴和不断抬头的保护主义正在颠覆数十年的自由贸易。从英国到新加坡，较小的国家正在落后。 <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834926/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="印度尼西亚莫罗瓦利工业园附近交通中的工人，该工业园是镍相关产业的中心。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>印度尼西亚莫罗瓦利工业园附近交通中的工人，该工业园是镍相关产业的中心。 Ulet Ifansasti/Getty Images <span>Ulet Ifansasti/Getty Images</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129598"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129598"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ed-ballard" itemprop="url" rel="author">艾德·巴拉德</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jason-douglas" itemprop="url" rel="author">杰森·道格拉斯</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jon-emont" itemprop="url" rel="author">乔恩·埃蒙特</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 12:01 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-economy-economic-losers-fba30b53"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>世界上最大的经济体在一场残酷的竞争中提供巨额补贴，以赢得未来的产业。失败者：所有付不起钱的国家。</p><p>针对制造电池、太阳能设备和其他绿色技术的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/climate-legislation-inflation-reduction-act-small-towns-eb0ce798?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">新税收抵免</a>正在吸引<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-biggest-winners-in-americas-climate-law-foreign-companies-c672e09d" target="_blank" class="icon none">大量资金</a>涌入美国，欧盟正试图以自己的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-to-unveil-clean-tech-plans-in-bid-to-rival-u-s-china-a391ef5a" target="_blank" class="icon none">绿色能源</a>支持计划来应对。日本宣布计划借债 1500 亿美元，为绿色技术投资浪潮提供资金。所有这些国家都在努力<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-eu-advance-buyers-club-for-ev-battery-minerals-5288287e" target="_blank" class="icon none">减少对中国的依赖</a>，中国在电池和制造电池的矿物等领域处于领先地位。</p><p>现在，一些规模较小的企业正在被抛在后面。许多经济体都是灵活的经济体，在几十年的自由贸易中不断崛起，但在激进的产业政策新时代却处于不利地位。英国和新加坡等工业化国家在提供补贴方面缺乏与最大经济集团竞争的规模。印度尼西亚等新兴市场原本希望利用<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/electric-vehicles-batteries-nickel-pickle-indonesia-9152b1f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其自然资源</a>来攀登经济阶梯，但也受到了这种转变的威胁。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834966?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>德国政府向英特尔提供了 110 亿美元的补贴，用于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwans-tsmc-to-build-first-european-chip-plant-in-germany-155e4d8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">建设两座半导体工厂</a>，总理奥拉夫·肖尔茨 (Olaf Scholz) 称这是德国历史上最大的外国直接投资。政府承诺的融资远高于新加坡贸工部的年度预算。</p><p> “让我坦白地告诉你们：我们承担不起比大公司出价更高的代价，”副总理黄循财在最近的一次政治集会上对支持者说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834210?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">英特尔首席执行官帕特·基辛格(Pat Gelsinger)和德国总理奥拉夫·舒尔茨(Olaf Scholz)于6月签署了一项协议，让英特尔在德国建造两家半导体工厂。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Chris Emil JanssEn/ddp/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>对于许多在英国培育的科技公司来说，增长在于其他地方。英国电池技术初创公司 Nexeon 在政府资助的帮助下在牛津附近开发了自己的技术，去年筹集了超过 2 亿美元。它的第一家商业工厂将设在韩国，随后可能会在北美设立一家工厂。</p><p> “但遗憾的是，英国不是这样，”纳科星公司首席执行官斯科特·布朗(Scott Brown)表示。如果政府不加大对电池行业的支持，纳科星公司并不认为这种情况会发生改变。</p><p>英国为数不多的本土电池制造商之一<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/UK/XLON/AMTE" class="">AMTE Power</a>表示<span class="company-name-type">，</span>鉴于美国和欧洲提供的补贴存在差异，该公司可能会重新考虑在苏格兰设立一家耗资 2 亿多美元的工厂的计划。电动汽车初创公司 Arrival 去年表示，以税收优惠为由，希望将生产重点放在美国而不是英国。</p><p>作为《通货膨胀削减法案》的一部分，美国为清洁能源提供了 3690 亿美元的激励措施和资金， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-green-subsidies-are-attracting-billions-of-dollars-to-red-states-11674488426?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">外国投资也带来了意外之财</a>。德国汽车制造商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/XE/XETR/BMW" class="company-name">宝马</a>刚刚在南卡罗来纳州破土动工建设一座新电池工厂。韩国公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hyundai-motor-lg-energy-to-build-4-3-bln-battery-jv-in-u-s-97991f73?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">现代和</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/KR/XKRX/066570" class="company-name">LG</a>宣布斥资 43 亿美元在佐治亚州建设电池厂。日本松下公司正在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/panasonic-energy-kansas-to-partner-on-4-billion-ev-battery-factory-11657754596?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">堪萨斯州建设一家工厂</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834214?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">工人们正在为堪萨斯州德索托附近的松下电动汽车电池工厂进行场地准备。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：查理·里德尔/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>解除全球化</h3><p>补贴竞赛标志着几十年来打破国家间贸易和投资壁垒的经济一体化又迈出了一步。</p><p>全球化将韩国和台湾等曾经贫穷的国家转变为高科技发达经济体，使数亿人摆脱了贫困。西方消费者获得了大量负担得起的消费品和更高的生活水平。技术进步和新的管理理念以及商品和金融资源也更加自由地在国家之间流动。</p><p>该模型的成本也很高。随着制造业工作转移到亚洲或前苏联国家，美国和西欧曾经繁荣的社区变得空心化。随着全球经济消耗更多的自然资源，环境问题日益凸显。随着外国资金涌入和流出，一些经济体面临着不稳定的资本外逃。</p><p>经济学家表示，放松全球一体化——无论是出于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/friend-shoring-might-be-bad-for-global-growth-inflation-11654437600?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">国家安全、地缘政治竞争还是供应链焦虑</a>的原因——都会带来自身的问题。尤其面临风险的是较小的发展中经济体，如果它们想要通过贸易实现更大的繁荣，就需要进入全球市场。</p><p> “整个世界正在变得更加内向，并远离开放的贸易和投资，”前美国财政部官员、资产管理公司 TCW Group 新兴市场董事总经理戴维·洛文格 (David Loevinger) 表示。 “欧洲、美国和中国正在进行补贴竞争，而这场竞争的失败者是财政资源较少的较贫穷经济体。”</p><p>对于那些希望利用绿色技术来推动本国经济发展的国家来说，西方对产业政策的拥抱可能尤其痛苦。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834220?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Harita 在印度尼西亚经营的镍加工厂的一名工人。印度尼西亚希望利用其镍资源打造世界领先的电池产业。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的 Ulet Ifansasti</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Indonesia has ambitions to parlay its <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/electric-vehicles-batteries-nickel-pickle-indonesia-9152b1f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">abundant nickel resources</a> into a world-leading battery industry.但作为爱尔兰共和军的一部分制定的美国规定，拒绝向含有大量来自非美国自由贸易伙伴国家的矿物的电动汽车电池提供补贴。印度尼西亚就是其中之一。</p><p> “我们拥有所有的自然资源。我们有人力资源。我们是一个民主国家，”说</p>印度尼西亚工商会会长阿尔斯贾德·拉吉德（Arsjad Rasjid）接受采访。 “请不要关闭我们。”<p></p><h3>获奖者</h3><p>作为补贴竞赛的领先者，美国正在经历投资热潮。根据联合国的数据，美国去年吸收了全球约 22% 的外国直接投资，成为全球最大的接受国。这略低于 2021 年全球投资在疫情期间暂停后反弹时的 26%，但明显高于 2019 年的 13%。5 月份与制造业相关的建筑支出与 2019 年相比增长了 76%。人口普查局数据显示，去年同期经季节调整后的年增长率为 1,940 亿美元。</p><p>在英国，纳科星公司的资金凸显了美国财力扭曲竞争环境的力量。除了去年筹集的私人资本外，Nexeon 还从英国政府电动汽车行业基金处获得了 200 万英镑，价值约 255 万美元。</p><p>几周后，根据 2021 年基础设施法引入的电池行业资助计划，Sila Nanotechnologies 和 Group14 Technologies 这两家美国竞争对手都从能源部获得了 1 亿美元的资金。与 Nexeon 一样，这些公司正在生产用于电池阳极的硅基材料，以提高性能。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="458" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834213?width=700&amp;height=458" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">北卡罗来纳州达勒姆市的一家半导体制造商 Wolfspeed 的工人们正在观看美国总统乔·拜登 (JoeBiden) 的讲话，这是他三月份美国投资之旅的一部分。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：梅丽莎·苏·格里茨/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>澳大利亚央行前副行长、西澳大利亚矿业公司 Fortescue <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AU/XASX/FMG" class="">Metals</a>旗下绿色能源部门 Fortescue Future Industries 现任董事盖伊·德贝尔 (Guy Debelle) 表示，“美国项目的经济性简直令人难以想象<span class="company-name-type">。</span> ” Debelle 表示，该公司正在寻找投资机会，目前认为美国是最有可能的投资地点，因为美国的补贴可能会使项目的价格降低高达 60%。</p><p>欧盟正在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eu-to-compete-with-u-s-clean-tech-tax-breaks-by-loosening-subsidy-rules-87a7d334?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">准备自己的一揽子支持计划</a>，放宽成员国给予工业的补贴限制。到 2030 年，欧盟希望绿色转型所需的 40% 关键技术在欧盟生产，包括太阳能设备（目前由中国主导的行业）、风力涡轮机和电池。</p><p>据 Benchmark Minerals Intelligence 估计，自 IRA 宣布以来，衡量在建项目产能的美国电池生产线已增长 67%，目前与欧洲的规模相当，欧洲同期增长了 26%。收集行业数据的英国公司。</p><h3>英国脱欧问题</h3><p>对于英国来说，全球贸易的转变发生在一个特别尴尬的时刻，英国在 2020 年离开欧盟后<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-prime-minister-rishi-sunak-tries-free-market-recipe-to-fix-britains-woes-2aa177b8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一直在努力</a>制定全球经济的新路线，这意味着它不再能够轻松进入其庞大的单一市场。</p><p>英国脱欧支持者表示，英国可以与其他国家达成双边贸易协议，并加大全球化力度。此后，自由贸易的势头陷入停滞，现在似乎正在倒退。</p><p>哥伦比亚商学院气候经济学家格诺特·瓦格纳表示：“在英国脱欧公投期间，没有人知道我们会看到美国产业政策的复苏。”</p><p>现在，英国政府面临着来自国内经济各个角落的呼吁，要求通过重振产业战略来应对全球经济的干预主义转向。</p><p>英国汽车业近期得到提振，捷豹路虎母公司选择<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-cinches-5-billion-ev-battery-plant-as-race-for-green-investments-heats-up-e20b142f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在英国新建电动电池工厂</a>，但绿色补贴总体规模远远落后于美国</p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="463" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834215?width=700&amp;height=463" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">英国财政部长杰里米·亨特面临着引入重振工业战略以应对全球经济干预主义转向的压力。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Tayfun Salci/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>财政部长杰里米·亨特承诺在今年秋天公布英国的应对措施，但淡化了预期，并表示英国不会“在一些扭曲性的全球补贴竞赛中与我们的朋友和盟友针锋相对”。他表示，英国将寻求将资金投向英国具有明显竞争优势的领域。</p><h3>新联盟</h3><p>前世界银行贸易专家查德·鲍恩表示，对于无法竞争的国家来说，一个解决方案是拉近富裕贸易伙伴的距离，并从其产业政策中受益，就像加拿大和墨西哥通过与美国的自由贸易协定所做的那样华盛顿特区智库彼得森国际经济研究所的官员表示，印度尼西亚政府正在参与美国主导的印度-太平洋经济繁荣框架，该经济协定希望能够改善其矿产的市场准入。</p><p>去年，投资部长巴利勒·拉哈达利亚 (Bahlil Lahadalia) 表示，印度尼西亚将寻求组建一个<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mineral-rich-developing-nations-demand-bigger-piece-of-the-ev-pie-d1421603?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">类似欧佩克 (OPEC) 的镍镍卡特尔组织</a>，以回应电动汽车制造国的保护主义。镍是一种电池矿物，印度尼西亚的产量占主导地位。欧佩克模式的组织将与其他主要出口国协调镍生产水平，以确保价格上涨。</p><p>分析师对该计划表示怀疑，部分原因是其他镍生产商不想疏远美国和中国等强大的贸易伙伴。拉丁美洲的左翼领导人也提出了类似欧佩克的锂生产商组织的想法，但尚未付诸实施。</p><p>印度尼西亚和津巴布韦对镍、铝土矿和锂等矿产实施了出口限制，并要求外国公司在该国建立加工设施，作为出口的条件。</p><p> “我不喜欢这些政策，但它们显然很受欢迎，”瑞士圣加仑大学国际贸易和经济发展教授西蒙·埃文内特(Simon Evenett)说。 “显然，这会推高价格，并增加不确定性和风险。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834218?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Harita 在印度尼西亚经营的镍加工综合体的景观。印度尼西亚和津巴布韦对镍和其他矿物实施了出口限制。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的 Ulet Ifansasti</p></figcaption></figure></div><p class="articleTagLine"> —伦敦的大卫·卢诺 (David Luhnow) 和悉尼的斯图尔特·康迪 (Stuart Condie) 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给Ed Ballard（ <a href="mailto:ed.ballard@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ed.ballard@wsj.com）</a> 、Jason Douglas（ <a href="mailto:jason.douglas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jason.douglas@wsj.com）</a>和Jon Emont（ <a href="mailto:jonathan.emont@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jonathan.emont@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 04:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-economy-economic-losers-fba30b53</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-economy-economic-losers-fba30b53<author><![CDATA[Ed BallardJason DouglasJon Emont]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>领导者</category><category>机械</category><category>电池</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>可再生能源设备</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>容量/设施</category><category>政府援助/赠款</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算/税收</category><category>贸易/外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>可持续发展/可持续发展</category><category>贸易壁垒/限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>容量</category><category>设施</category><category>政府援助</category><category>赠款</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算</category><category>税收</category><category>贸易</category><category>外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>政治</category><category>可持续发展</category><category>可持续性</category><category>贸易壁垒</category><category>限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>factiva filters</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>机械</category><category>电池</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>可再生能源设备</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Economic Losers in the New World Order]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>巨额补贴和不断抬头的保护主义正在颠覆数十年的自由贸易。从英国到新加坡，较小的国家正在落后。 <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834926/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="印度尼西亚莫罗瓦利工业园附近交通中的工人，该工业园是镍相关产业的中心。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>印度尼西亚莫罗瓦利工业园附近交通中的工人，该工业园是镍相关产业的中心。 Ulet Ifansasti/Getty Images <span>Ulet Ifansasti/Getty Images</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129598"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129598"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ed-ballard" itemprop="url" rel="author">艾德·巴拉德</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jason-douglas" itemprop="url" rel="author">杰森·道格拉斯</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jon-emont" itemprop="url" rel="author">乔恩·埃蒙特</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 12:01 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-economy-economic-losers-fba30b53"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>世界上最大的经济体在一场残酷的竞争中提供巨额补贴，以赢得未来的产业。失败者：所有付不起钱的国家。</p><p>针对制造电池、太阳能设备和其他绿色技术的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/climate-legislation-inflation-reduction-act-small-towns-eb0ce798?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">新税收抵免</a>正在吸引<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-biggest-winners-in-americas-climate-law-foreign-companies-c672e09d" target="_blank" class="icon none">大量资金</a>涌入美国，欧盟正试图以自己的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-to-unveil-clean-tech-plans-in-bid-to-rival-u-s-china-a391ef5a" target="_blank" class="icon none">绿色能源</a>支持计划来应对。日本宣布计划借债 1500 亿美元，为绿色技术投资浪潮提供资金。所有这些国家都在努力<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-eu-advance-buyers-club-for-ev-battery-minerals-5288287e" target="_blank" class="icon none">减少对中国的依赖</a>，中国在电池和制造电池的矿物等领域处于领先地位。</p><p>现在，一些规模较小的企业正在被抛在后面。许多经济体都是灵活的经济体，在几十年的自由贸易中不断崛起，但在激进的产业政策新时代却处于不利地位。英国和新加坡等工业化国家在提供补贴方面缺乏与最大经济集团竞争的规模。印度尼西亚等新兴市场原本希望利用<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/electric-vehicles-batteries-nickel-pickle-indonesia-9152b1f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其自然资源</a>来攀登经济阶梯，但也受到了这种转变的威胁。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834966?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>德国政府向英特尔提供了 110 亿美元的补贴，用于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwans-tsmc-to-build-first-european-chip-plant-in-germany-155e4d8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">建设两座半导体工厂</a>，总理奥拉夫·肖尔茨 (Olaf Scholz) 称这是德国历史上最大的外国直接投资。政府承诺的融资远高于新加坡贸工部的年度预算。</p><p> “让我坦白地告诉你们：我们承担不起比大公司出价更高的代价，”副总理黄循财在最近的一次政治集会上对支持者说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834210?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">英特尔首席执行官帕特·基辛格(Pat Gelsinger)和德国总理奥拉夫·舒尔茨(Olaf Scholz)于6月签署了一项协议，让英特尔在德国建造两家半导体工厂。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Chris Emil JanssEn/ddp/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>对于许多在英国培育的科技公司来说，增长在于其他地方。英国电池技术初创公司 Nexeon 在政府资助的帮助下在牛津附近开发了自己的技术，去年筹集了超过 2 亿美元。它的第一家商业工厂将设在韩国，随后可能会在北美设立一家工厂。</p><p> “但遗憾的是，英国不是这样，”纳科星公司首席执行官斯科特·布朗(Scott Brown)表示。如果政府不加大对电池行业的支持，纳科星公司并不认为这种情况会发生改变。</p><p>英国为数不多的本土电池制造商之一<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/UK/XLON/AMTE" class="">AMTE Power</a>表示<span class="company-name-type">，</span>鉴于美国和欧洲提供的补贴存在差异，该公司可能会重新考虑在苏格兰设立一家耗资 2 亿多美元的工厂的计划。电动汽车初创公司 Arrival 去年表示，以税收优惠为由，希望将生产重点放在美国而不是英国。</p><p>作为《通货膨胀削减法案》的一部分，美国为清洁能源提供了 3690 亿美元的激励措施和资金， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-green-subsidies-are-attracting-billions-of-dollars-to-red-states-11674488426?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">外国投资也带来了意外之财</a>。德国汽车制造商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/XE/XETR/BMW" class="company-name">宝马</a>刚刚在南卡罗来纳州破土动工建设一座新电池工厂。韩国公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hyundai-motor-lg-energy-to-build-4-3-bln-battery-jv-in-u-s-97991f73?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">现代和</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/KR/XKRX/066570" class="company-name">LG</a>宣布斥资 43 亿美元在佐治亚州建设电池厂。日本松下公司正在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/panasonic-energy-kansas-to-partner-on-4-billion-ev-battery-factory-11657754596?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">堪萨斯州建设一家工厂</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834214?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">工人们正在为堪萨斯州德索托附近的松下电动汽车电池工厂进行场地准备。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：查理·里德尔/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>解除全球化</h3><p>补贴竞赛标志着几十年来打破国家间贸易和投资壁垒的经济一体化又迈出了一步。</p><p>全球化将韩国和台湾等曾经贫穷的国家转变为高科技发达经济体，使数亿人摆脱了贫困。西方消费者获得了大量负担得起的消费品和更高的生活水平。技术进步和新的管理理念以及商品和金融资源也更加自由地在国家之间流动。</p><p>该模型的成本也很高。随着制造业工作转移到亚洲或前苏联国家，美国和西欧曾经繁荣的社区变得空心化。随着全球经济消耗更多的自然资源，环境问题日益凸显。随着外国资金涌入和流出，一些经济体面临着不稳定的资本外逃。</p><p>经济学家表示，放松全球一体化——无论是出于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/friend-shoring-might-be-bad-for-global-growth-inflation-11654437600?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">国家安全、地缘政治竞争还是供应链焦虑</a>的原因——都会带来自身的问题。尤其面临风险的是较小的发展中经济体，如果它们想要通过贸易实现更大的繁荣，就需要进入全球市场。</p><p> “整个世界正在变得更加内向，并远离开放的贸易和投资，”前美国财政部官员、资产管理公司 TCW Group 新兴市场董事总经理戴维·洛文格 (David Loevinger) 表示。 “欧洲、美国和中国正在进行补贴竞争，而这场竞争的失败者是财政资源较少的较贫穷经济体。”</p><p>对于那些希望利用绿色技术来推动本国经济发展的国家来说，西方对产业政策的拥抱可能尤其痛苦。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834220?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Harita 在印度尼西亚经营的镍加工厂的一名工人。印度尼西亚希望利用其镍资源打造世界领先的电池产业。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的 Ulet Ifansasti</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Indonesia has ambitions to parlay its <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/electric-vehicles-batteries-nickel-pickle-indonesia-9152b1f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">abundant nickel resources</a> into a world-leading battery industry.但作为爱尔兰共和军的一部分制定的美国规定，拒绝向含有大量来自非美国自由贸易伙伴国家的矿物的电动汽车电池提供补贴。印度尼西亚就是其中之一。</p><p> “我们拥有所有的自然资源。我们有人力资源。我们是一个民主国家，”说</p>印度尼西亚工商会会长阿尔斯贾德·拉吉德（Arsjad Rasjid）接受采访。 “请不要关闭我们。”<p></p><h3>获奖者</h3><p>作为补贴竞赛的领先者，美国正在经历投资热潮。根据联合国的数据，美国去年吸收了全球约 22% 的外国直接投资，成为全球最大的接受国。这略低于 2021 年全球投资在疫情期间暂停后反弹时的 26%，但明显高于 2019 年的 13%。5 月份与制造业相关的建筑支出与 2019 年相比增长了 76%。人口普查局数据显示，去年同期经季节调整后的年增长率为 1,940 亿美元。</p><p>在英国，纳科星公司的资金凸显了美国财力扭曲竞争环境的力量。除了去年筹集的私人资本外，Nexeon 还从英国政府电动汽车行业基金处获得了 200 万英镑，价值约 255 万美元。</p><p>几周后，根据 2021 年基础设施法引入的电池行业资助计划，Sila Nanotechnologies 和 Group14 Technologies 这两家美国竞争对手都从能源部获得了 1 亿美元的资金。与 Nexeon 一样，这些公司正在生产用于电池阳极的硅基材料，以提高性能。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="458" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834213?width=700&amp;height=458" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">北卡罗来纳州达勒姆市的一家半导体制造商 Wolfspeed 的工人们正在观看美国总统乔·拜登 (JoeBiden) 的讲话，这是他三月份美国投资之旅的一部分。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：梅丽莎·苏·格里茨/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>澳大利亚央行前副行长、西澳大利亚矿业公司 Fortescue <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AU/XASX/FMG" class="">Metals</a>旗下绿色能源部门 Fortescue Future Industries 现任董事盖伊·德贝尔 (Guy Debelle) 表示，“美国项目的经济性简直令人难以想象<span class="company-name-type">。</span> ” Debelle 表示，该公司正在寻找投资机会，目前认为美国是最有可能的投资地点，因为美国的补贴可能会使项目的价格降低高达 60%。</p><p>欧盟正在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eu-to-compete-with-u-s-clean-tech-tax-breaks-by-loosening-subsidy-rules-87a7d334?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">准备自己的一揽子支持计划</a>，放宽成员国给予工业的补贴限制。到 2030 年，欧盟希望绿色转型所需的 40% 关键技术在欧盟生产，包括太阳能设备（目前由中国主导的行业）、风力涡轮机和电池。</p><p>据 Benchmark Minerals Intelligence 估计，自 IRA 宣布以来，衡量在建项目产能的美国电池生产线已增长 67%，目前与欧洲的规模相当，欧洲同期增长了 26%。收集行业数据的英国公司。</p><h3>英国脱欧问题</h3><p>对于英国来说，全球贸易的转变发生在一个特别尴尬的时刻，英国在 2020 年离开欧盟后<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-prime-minister-rishi-sunak-tries-free-market-recipe-to-fix-britains-woes-2aa177b8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一直在努力</a>制定全球经济的新路线，这意味着它不再能够轻松进入其庞大的单一市场。</p><p>英国脱欧支持者表示，英国可以与其他国家达成双边贸易协议，并加大全球化力度。此后，自由贸易的势头陷入停滞，现在似乎正在倒退。</p><p>哥伦比亚商学院气候经济学家格诺特·瓦格纳表示：“在英国脱欧公投期间，没有人知道我们会看到美国产业政策的复苏。”</p><p>现在，英国政府面临着来自国内经济各个角落的呼吁，要求通过重振产业战略来应对全球经济的干预主义转向。</p><p>英国汽车业近期得到提振，捷豹路虎母公司选择<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-cinches-5-billion-ev-battery-plant-as-race-for-green-investments-heats-up-e20b142f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在英国新建电动电池工厂</a>，但绿色补贴总体规模远远落后于美国</p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="463" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834215?width=700&amp;height=463" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">英国财政部长杰里米·亨特面临着引入重振工业战略以应对全球经济干预主义转向的压力。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Tayfun Salci/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>财政部长杰里米·亨特承诺在今年秋天公布英国的应对措施，但淡化了预期，并表示英国不会“在一些扭曲性的全球补贴竞赛中与我们的朋友和盟友针锋相对”。他表示，英国将寻求将资金投向英国具有明显竞争优势的领域。</p><h3>新联盟</h3><p>前世界银行贸易专家查德·鲍恩表示，对于无法竞争的国家来说，一个解决方案是拉近富裕贸易伙伴的距离，并从其产业政策中受益，就像加拿大和墨西哥通过与美国的自由贸易协定所做的那样华盛顿特区智库彼得森国际经济研究所的官员表示，印度尼西亚政府正在参与美国主导的印度-太平洋经济繁荣框架，该经济协定希望能够改善其矿产的市场准入。</p><p>去年，投资部长巴利勒·拉哈达利亚 (Bahlil Lahadalia) 表示，印度尼西亚将寻求组建一个<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mineral-rich-developing-nations-demand-bigger-piece-of-the-ev-pie-d1421603?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">类似欧佩克 (OPEC) 的镍镍卡特尔组织</a>，以回应电动汽车制造国的保护主义。镍是一种电池矿物，印度尼西亚的产量占主导地位。欧佩克模式的组织将与其他主要出口国协调镍生产水平，以确保价格上涨。</p><p>分析师对该计划表示怀疑，部分原因是其他镍生产商不想疏远美国和中国等强大的贸易伙伴。拉丁美洲的左翼领导人也提出了类似欧佩克的锂生产商组织的想法，但尚未付诸实施。</p><p>印度尼西亚和津巴布韦对镍、铝土矿和锂等矿产实施了出口限制，并要求外国公司在该国建立加工设施，作为出口的条件。</p><p> “我不喜欢这些政策，但它们显然很受欢迎，”瑞士圣加仑大学国际贸易和经济发展教授西蒙·埃文内特(Simon Evenett)说。 “显然，这会推高价格，并增加不确定性和风险。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834218?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Harita 在印度尼西亚经营的镍加工综合体的景观。印度尼西亚和津巴布韦对镍和其他矿物实施了出口限制。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的 Ulet Ifansasti</p></figcaption></figure></div><p class="articleTagLine"> —伦敦的大卫·卢诺 (David Luhnow) 和悉尼的斯图尔特·康迪 (Stuart Condie) 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给Ed Ballard（ <a href="mailto:ed.ballard@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ed.ballard@wsj.com）</a> 、Jason Douglas（ <a href="mailto:jason.douglas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jason.douglas@wsj.com）</a>和Jon Emont（ <a href="mailto:jonathan.emont@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jonathan.emont@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 04:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-economy-economic-losers-fba30b53</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-economy-economic-losers-fba30b53<author><![CDATA[Ed BallardJason DouglasJon Emont]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>领导者</category><category>机械</category><category>电池</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>可再生能源设备</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>容量/设施</category><category>政府援助/赠款</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算/税收</category><category>贸易/外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>可持续发展/可持续发展</category><category>贸易壁垒/限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>容量</category><category>设施</category><category>政府援助</category><category>赠款</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算</category><category>税收</category><category>贸易</category><category>外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>政治</category><category>可持续发展</category><category>可持续性</category><category>贸易壁垒</category><category>限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>factiva filters</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>机械</category><category>电池</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>可再生能源设备</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Office Woes and China’s Slowdown Rattle Singapore’s REIT Market]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>一些房地产信托经理在其资产价值下跌后要求监管机构放宽杠杆限制<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833779/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="过去二十年来，新加坡吸引了数十家房地产信托公司上市，并已成为日本以外最大的亚洲房地产投资信托市场。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>过去二十年来，新加坡吸引了数十家房地产信托公司上市，并已成为日本以外最大的亚洲房地产投资信托市场。罗斯兰·拉赫曼/法新社/盖蒂图片<span>社 罗斯兰·拉赫曼/法新社/盖蒂图片社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001127782"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001127782"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">很快<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/weilun-soon" itemprop="url" rel="author">伟伦</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 14 日上午 12:00（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-office-woes-and-chinas-slowdown-rattle-singapores-reit-market-e1367051"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>新加坡——亚洲最大的房地产投资信托市场之一正受到美国办公楼低迷和中国经济放缓的影响。</p><p>新加坡730亿美元的公开上市房地产投资信托市场最近受到震动，此前宏利经营的一家美国办公信托7月份表示，其投资组合价值<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/stock-market-today-dow-jones-07-18-2023/card/u-s-office-slump-rocks-a-real-estate-investment-trust-in-singapore-E6tW4F1BthU0D66a71kW?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在2023年上半年下降了15%</a> ，导致其违反了贷款契约。该公司和另外两家专注于美国商业地产的公司在过去一年中损失了三分之二以上的总市值。</p><p>市场参与者担心宏利美国房地产投资信托基金的困境只是冰山一角。随着中国宏观经济前景恶化，一些在新加坡上市、持有中国商业地产的房地产投资信托基金的股价今年也出现下跌。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="960" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833994?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>在华南地区拥有购物中心的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SG/XSES/CEDU" class="">大信商用信托</a>表示<span class="company-name-type">，</span>其部分租户，包括中国连锁超市家乐福运营商，已提前终止租约。该公司还在 7 月份透露，其投资组合的价值将在 2022 年下降。</p><p>据知情人士透露，一些信托管理公司最近要求新加坡最高金融监管机构新加坡金融管理局放宽杠杆限制，以便让他们在与银行协商贷款条款时拥有更大的财务灵活性。新加坡房地产投资信托基金的债务资产比率通常必须保持在 45% 以内。</p><p>金管局发言人表示，它密切关注宏观经济状况，并定期与业界进行讨论。该发言人补充说，如果信托因其财产价值下降而超过杠杆限制，则不会构成违规。</p><p>过去二十年来，新加坡吸引了数十家房地产信托公司上市，并已成为日本以外最大的亚洲房地产投资信托市场。这些股票合计占新加坡股市总市值的 12%。最近美国房地产估值和股价的下跌正在成为对市场弹性的考验。大多数专注于中国的房地产投资信托基金尚未报告出现此类下降，但分析师表示，人们担心<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-stutters-forward-as-growth-concerns-linger-1be8acb2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国复苏乏力</a>的影响将开始影响一些信托持有的购物中心和工业园区的入住率及其估值。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="395" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833780?width=700&amp;height=395" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">大信商用信托表示，其部分租户，包括连锁超市家乐福的中国运营商，已提前终止租约。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Cfoto/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “市场上有一种紧张感，”新加坡兴业银行房地产投资信托基金分析师 Vijay Natarajan 表示。他表示，造成这种情况的因素有很多，包括利率快速上升以及疫情对海外房产的影响。他补充说，这些发展对新加坡的国际房地产投资信托基金产生了不成比例的影响，因为它们的投资组合规模往往较小，且多元化程度较低。</p><p>在美国，许多办公室职员<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-return-to-the-office-has-stalled-e0af9741?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">拒绝重返工作场所</a>，导致公司重新考虑他们所需的办公空间大小。这反过来又导致写字楼房地产投资信托基金和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/stock-prices-of-office-landlords-plummet-as-short-sellers-pile-in-9373fc95" target="_blank" class="icon none">写字楼业主股票</a>的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-hottest-real-estate-play-is-in-your-neighborhood-7e8ff991" target="_blank" class="icon none">估值</a>走低。</p><p>宏利美国房地产投资信托基金在洛杉矶、亚特兰大和华盛顿特区等美国主要城市或附近拥有建筑物</p><p>该信托最近寻求对其投资组合进行独立估值，其管理人员惊讶地发现投资组合已下跌 2.8 亿美元，降至 16.3 亿美元。</p><p>该信托公司位于宾夕法尼亚大道 1750 号的大楼距离白宫仅一个街区，美国政府为其主要租户，其价值为 1.24 亿美元，而 2022 年底为 1.56 亿美元。</p><p>例如，根据仲量联行旗下子公司提供的估值，该公司位于新泽西州<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/JLL" class="">锡</a>考克斯广场大道 500 号的 11 层办公楼截至 6 月底价值 6,700 万美元，较六个月前下降 27% <span class="company-name-type">。</span>仅 7 英里之外，其位于泽西市 10 Exchange Place 的办公楼价值 2.58 亿美元，较 2022 年底下降 11%。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="501" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833782?width=700&amp;height=501" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">新泽西州泽西城交易广场景观</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：蒂莫西·A.克拉里/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>整体价值损失，加上利率急剧上升，增加了借贷成本，导致信托公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/stock-market-today-dow-jones-07-18-2023/card/u-s-office-slump-rocks-a-real-estate-investment-trust-in-singapore-E6tW4F1BthU0D66a71kW?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">违反了其中一项财务契约</a>。宏利美国房地产投资信托基金上半年没有进行现金分配。该公司周一表示，其管理人已付款，以小幅降低其杠杆率，并正在与贷方就放弃违反契约的事宜进行谈判。它还可能出售亚特兰大的菲普斯大厦办公楼，以帮助增强其流动性。</p><p>该房地产投资信托基金的股价周一进一步下跌。在过去的一个月里，它们的价值缩水了近一半。宏利美国房地产投资信托基金副首席执行官卡罗琳·方表示，该信托基金还在考虑向第三方出售其他资产。</p><p>鉴于上半年估值大幅下跌，星展银行分析师表示，可能需要信托发起人的财务支持来帮助解决问题。他们表示，这可能采取股权注入或资产出售的形式。</p><p>新加坡其他专注于美国和中国的房地产投资信托基金最近公布了收益，但没有在年中披露时对其房产进行外部估值。许多车辆这样做只是为了全年业绩。</p><p>写信给孙伟伦<a href="mailto:weilun.soon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">weilun.soon@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-office-woes-and-chinas-slowdown-rattle-singapores-reit-market-e1367051</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-office-woes-and-chinas-slowdown-rattle-singapores-reit-market-e1367051<author><![CDATA[Weilun Soon]]></author><category> wsjfinance-asia</category><category>商业地产</category><category>信托/基金/金融工具</category><category>投资信托</category><category>房地产投资信托</category><category>保险</category><category>人寿保险</category><category>房地产/建筑</category><category>金融服务</category><category>Investing/Securities</category><category> Residential REITs</category><category>房地产</category><category>零售房地产投资信托基金</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>商业房地产</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>大信商用信托</category><category>新加坡CEDU</category><category> SG:CEDU</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>信托</category><category>资金</category><category>金融工具</category><category>投资信托</category><category>房地产投资信托</category><category>保险</category><category>人寿保险</category><category>房地产</category><category>建造</category><category>financial services</category><category> investing</category><category> securities</category><category>住宅房地产投资信托基金</category><category>零售房地产投资信托基金</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Police Raid Small Kansas Newspaper]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Search triggered by document with personal information about a local restaurateur <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001131557"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834786?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The Marion County Record is in a 1,900-person city, about an hour&#39;s drive north of Wichita.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Mark Reinstein/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001131557"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/shannon-najmabadi" itemprop="url" rel="author">Shannon Najmabadi</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated Aug. 13, 2023 10:20 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/police-raid-small-kansas-paper-seizing-phones-computers-3f7d5891"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> The police force of a small Kansas town raided the office of a local newspaper and the home of its owners on Friday, seizing personal cellphones and computers in a case US legal experts say is likely unprecedented in modern times.</p><p> One of the newspaper&#39;s owners, 98-year-old Joan Meyer, collapsed and died the next day, according to her son Eric Meyer, who is also a co-owner of the paper.</p><p> The search centered on a tip the news outlet, called the Marion County Record, received from a confidential source who alleged a local restaurateur, Kari Newell, was driving without a license after an impaired driving conviction 15 years ago. Record staff investigated the tip using a document the source provided but decided not to publish a story because they had reservations about the source&#39;s motives and how the source got the document, which contained personal information about Newell.</p><p> “That is what has all of my publishers going &#39;wait a minute, we&#39;re sent stuff all the time,&#39;” said Emily Bradbury, executive director of the Kansas Press Association. “If that is the catalyst for seizing my computers, this is scary.”</p><p> The Record is based about an hour&#39;s drive north of Wichita in the 1,900-person city of Marion. The Meyer family has owned the paper for 25 years.</p><p> A reporter with the Record received the tip about Newell in early August. The source sent a document—a copy of a letter addressed to Newell from the Kansas Department of Revenue—that included Newell&#39;s date of birth and driver&#39;s license, which the reporter used to verify the document&#39;s veracity on a state website. The reporter used her own name to do so, said Meyer, a former journalism professor and editor at the Milwaukee Journal. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834876?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Legal experts and advocates for press freedom said the raids likely violate a privacy-protection act Congress passed in 1980.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: John Hanna/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> But Meyer said he had suspected that the paper was “being set up—that somebody gave us a document that we weren&#39;t supposed to have.”</p><p> Without mentioning Newell&#39;s name, Meyer told the police and county sheriff about the document, said they didn&#39;t intend to publish a story and offered to provide additional information in an email, he said.</p><p> “We wanted to disclose that we had it,” he said. He didn&#39;t get a response, he said.</p><p> The next week, sheriff&#39;s deputies and police officers simultaneously showed up at the news outlet&#39;s office and at the house Meyer shared with his mother, with a search warrant signed by Eighth Judicial District Magistrate Judge Laura Viar. No probable-cause statement justifying the need for a search has been made public. Meyer&#39;s mother grew agitated as officers rifled through papers and took electronics, Meyer said.</p><p> The Eighth Judicial District said it couldn&#39;t comment on a matter pending before the court.</p><p> Marion Police Chief Gideon Cody responded to questions about the case by referring to the search warrant and a public statement that said he believed the judicial system would be vindicated once the entire story was made public.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “The victim asks that we do all the law allows to ensure justice is served. The Marion Kansas Police Department will [do] nothing less,” he said in the statement, also posted to the police department&#39;s Facebook page.</p><p> Newell said she was shocked to learn of the raid after being contacted by the police early last week. They said she might be the victim of a crime, because a reporter and editor at the Record received a copy of a letter she had received about her driver&#39;s license, Newell said.</p><p> “I don&#39;t know if it ever left their organization or not. But the fact that they were even considering—if they were not going to do a story on it, then what was the point of downloading it?” Newell said, adding that she believed the Record was an untrustworthy source of news.</p><p> She confirmed she had driven without a license but said she had a driver&#39;s license now.</p><p> “I am not the Gestapo. I can&#39;t go tell the police, &#39;Hey, go raid this place&#39; and they&#39;re just going to be like, &#39;OK, I&#39;m going to go do that after lunch.&#39; There is a full process that comes into play, none of which I had any thing or any part of,” she said.</p><p> Meyer said neither he nor the reporter who received the tip shared the personal information or downloaded it from the state website. It is standard practice to look into tips the newsroom receives, he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834875?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Eric Meyer, whose family has owned the Marion County Record for 25 years, took over as editor during the pandemic.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: John Hanna/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The Kansas Bureau of Investigation assigned an agent to the case on Tuesday, after getting a request from local police and the Marion County Attorney to join “an investigation into allegations of illegal access and dissemination of confidential criminal justice information,” said the agency&#39;s spokeswoman Melissa Underwood. The KBI agent didn&#39;t apply for the search warrants executed at the Record&#39;s office and Meyer&#39;s home, and wasn&#39;t present when they were served, Underwood said.</p><p> “Director [Tony] Mattivi believes very strongly that freedom of the press is a vanguard of American democracy,” she said, referencing the agency&#39;s director. “But another principle of our free society is equal application of the law.”</p><p> Legal experts and advocates for press freedom said the raids likely violate a privacy-protection act Congress passed in 1980 that requires law-enforcement officials to get a subpoena for reporters&#39; work product rather than a search warrant that cannot be challenged in court beforehand. There are exceptions if the journalists are believed to be involved in criminal activity.</p><p> “The subpoena gives newspapers the ability to go to court and ask the judge to either limit the scope of it or to totally quash it,” said Clay Calvert, an emeritus professor at the University of Florida with expertise in freedom of the press and freedom of speech issues. “This is definitely unique. I would call it an egregious and outrageous attack on small town journalism.”</p><p> Mark Johnson, who has represented media companies and reporters and taught First Amendment law at the University of Kansas journalism school, said the searches could have a chilling effect if they go unaddressed.</p><p> “If the press is to perform its function, it has to publish a lot of things that people don&#39;t like. And if they feel that they are going to be intimidated for doing things like that, then they&#39;ll be more reluctant to do it,” he said.</p><p> Meyer said the Record plans to file a federal lawsuit. The paper had investigated the police chief before he took office but didn&#39;t publish a story, Meyer said. Once Cody took office, he stopped providing a long-published blotter of law-enforcement activities, Meyer said.</p><p> Although the raid brought national attention, the paper has heard from few locals, Meyer said. “They&#39;re afraid in a small town that if they cross the powers that be, they will be punished.”</p><p> Meyer took over as editor of the Record during the pandemic, after he “got stranded” in his hometown of Marion. His father had worked at the Record starting in 1948 and purchased it with Meyer in 1998.</p><p> “I want to make sure that this gets enough publicity that people won&#39;t try to do it anywhere else,” he said. “But I regret the fact that that publicity has to make it look like this town that I&#39;m trying to help is a corrupt cesspool.”</p><p> Write to Shannon Najmabadi at <a href="mailto:shannon.najmabadi@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">shannon.najmabadi@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 02:20:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/police-raid-small-kansas-paper-seizing-phones-computers-3f7d5891</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/police-raid-small-kansas-paper-seizing-phones-computers-3f7d5891<author><![CDATA[Shannon Najmabadi]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>Human Rights/Civil Liberties</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>human rights</category><category> civil liberties </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Friend of Assassinated Presidential Candidate in Ecuador Replaces Him in Race]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>克里斯蒂安·苏里塔表示，他将继续打击费尔南多·比亚维森西奥领导的有组织犯罪和贩毒活动<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132008"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834924?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">克里斯蒂安·苏里塔（中）长期在厄瓜多尔担任调查记者，经常撰写有关政治腐败的文章。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：马丁·贝尔内蒂/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001132008"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ryan-dube" itemprop="url" rel="author">瑞安·杜贝</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 13 日晚上 8:27 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/friend-of-assassinated-presidential-candidate-in-ecuador-replaces-him-in-race-c6cbdc40"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Christian Zurita, a well-known investigative journalist, said Sunday he will run for president of Ecuador in place of his close friend and colleague Fernando Villavicencio, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">who was assassinated</a> Wednesday by gunmen.</p><p>身穿防弹背心的祖里塔表示，他将继续打击有组织犯罪和贩毒活动，这些活动已将这个拥有 1800 万人口的曾经和平的安第斯国家变成了拉丁美洲<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cocaine-trade-and-gang-violence-strike-hard-in-once-peaceful-ecuador-bad953c8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最暴力的国家</a>之一。</p><p> “费尔南多·比亚维森西奥的项目完好无损，我们将为他而战，”祖里塔在基多的新闻发布会上说。 “我们不会坐下来与任何黑手党谈判。我们只是不会这么做。”</p><p>苏里塔作为“建设运动”政党的候选人资格仍需得到厄瓜多尔选举当局的批准，分析人士称这应该是一种形式。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=3A297452-49E9-4885-AD64-0A664604940D&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ffriend-of-assassinated-presidential-candidate-in-ecuador-replaces-him-in-race-c6cbdc40&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Ecuadorean Presidential Candidate Fernando Villavicencio was shot dead as he left a campaign event in Quito, less than two weeks before the election. He was a sharp critic of corruption and said he had received threats from a local gang.照片：Shutterstock<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>苏里塔在厄瓜多尔担任调查记者很长时间，他经常撰写有关政治腐败的文章。他与比亚维森西奥密切合作，后者也是一名记者，因揭露腐败而名声大噪。这些人合作进行了大量调查并一起写书。</p><p>在竞选期间陪伴比亚维森西奥的苏里塔是最早公开比亚维森西奥被枪杀的人之一。他发布了混乱后果的视频，显示人们尖叫着，挤在地板上。</p><p> “他们杀了我的朋友，”周三，祖里塔在发布视频后不久在 X（该网站以前称为 Twitter）上写道。</p><p>与在决定竞选总统之前当选为国会议员的比亚维森西奥不同，苏里塔没有政治经验。由于 8 月 20 日将举行总统选举，在候选人需要于周四结束竞选活动之前，他几乎没有时间让选民知道他的名字。</p><p>基多政治风险咨询公司 Profitas 总裁塞巴斯蒂安·乌尔塔多 (Sebastian Hurtado) 表示：“候选人获得的选票将受到暗杀事件中产生的同情心的推动。” “作为比亚维森西奥的长期盟友，他也同样关注反腐败，他正在延续比亚维森西奥的遗产。”</p><p>比亚维森西奥周三在离开基多的一场竞选活动时头部中弹，他曾承诺追捕造成凶杀案激增的强大毒贩。据内政部称，自 2019 年以来，厄瓜多尔的凶杀案增加了四倍，去年达到创纪录的 4,800 起。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-assassination-reflects-rapid-rise-of-violent-cocaine-trade-aa27aedc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">暴力事件的起因是帮派之间为争夺通过厄瓜多尔运输可卡因的路线而发生</a>的战争，这些可卡因在邻国哥伦比亚生产，后来运往欧洲和美国</p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="462" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834925?width=700&amp;height=462" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">费尔南多·比亚维森西奥上周在基多的竞选集会上发表讲话。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：凯伦·托罗/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>比亚维森西奥曾承诺铲除腐败并清洗警察，称有组织犯罪腐蚀了政治机构和执法部门。</p><p> Days before he was killed, Villavicencio said he received threats from the leader of the Choneros prison gang, one of Ecuador&#39;s largest and most violent gangs.</p><p>周六，吉列尔莫·拉索总统的政府派遣了 4,000 名警察和士兵前往关押乔内罗斯领导人的监狱，以便将他转移到名为“岩石”的最高安全设施。拉索近日还表示，联邦调查局派出了一个团队协助调查。</p><p>六名<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-declares-state-of-emergency-after-presidential-candidate-killed-6e639e72?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">哥伦比亚嫌疑人因涉嫌暗杀比亚维森西奥而被捕</a>。警方称另一名嫌疑人枪杀了比亚维森西奥，他在与警察的枪战中受伤后死亡。</p><p> “厄瓜多尔将恢复和平与安全，”拉索周六在 X 上写道。</p><p>写信给 Ryan Dubé： <a href="mailto:ryan.dube@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ryan.dube@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 00:27:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/friend-of-assassminate-presidential-candidate-in-ecuador-replaces-him-in-race-c6cbdc40</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/friend-of-assassminate-presidential-candidate-in-ecuador-replaces-him-in-race-c6cbdc40<author><![CDATA[Ryan Dubé]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>general news</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><